commit.message:
CI: remove verbose flag when building

It's too verbose to spot errors/warnings. It's useful to debug
the flags passed to the compiler.

CI: use ninja to build

This makes it easier to read the build logs.

CI: use LLVM 18 instead of LLVM 17

Hopefully there's some new things for C++.

CI: use ubuntu-latest to run Alpine target

The setup-gcc/setup-clang scripts don't work with a more recent Ubuntu...

remove constexpr from DEFINE_xxx_CONTEXT()

It prevents from using DLL export (in libmatroska). We can set it locally when needed.
add an EbmlCallbacksMaster variant of tEBML_INFO_CONTEXT

add an EbmlMaster variant of tEBML_CONTEXT

Hopefully the compiler picks the most appropriate one ?

replace EBML_CLASS_CONTEXT with EBML_MASTER_CLASS_CONTEXT

It's only used with master element classes in mkvtoolnix of VLC.

This will make iterating through the class context children possible without any code change.

add EBML_MASTER_CLASS_CONTEXT to get the EbmlSemanticContextMaster of any master class

This is the counterpart to EBML_CLASS_CONTEXT for master elements.
use GetElementSpec() in EBML_INFO() which provides strongger typing

make the EbmlSemanticContextMaster definitions constexpr

Even though it's not very useful as a static member variable...

don't export Context_EbmlHead anymore

EbmlHead is public/shared class. One can call EbmlHead::GetContextMaster();
store the EbmlSemanticContextMaster as a static member for each EbmlMaster class
add comments about ORPHAN macros
add a static method to retrieve the EbmlSemanticContextMaster of any EbmlMaster
fix indentation

return EbmlSemanticContextMaster in global callbacks

It can only be context with a list of elements.

move the list of children in EbmlSemanticContextMaster

It doesn't make sense for other types on element/context.
The size if kept in the EbmlSemanticContext to notify when it's a master element.
add a specialized EbmlSemanticContext class for EbmlMaster
add a specialized EbmlCallbacks class for EbmlMaster
the DEFINE_xxx_MASTER macro is DEFINE_xxx_MASTER_CONS with a constructor
Merge remote-tracking branch 'robux4/typed_children3'

commit.message: provide a stronger typed version of EbmlStream::FindNextID()

use the const form of FindFirstElt/FindNextElt in helpers

If we don't want to create the element, we can use a const EbmlMaster

remove EbmlMaster::FindElt

It's a duplicate of EbmlMaster::FindFirstElt which is more often used.

Only VLC uses it and it can be easily switched for all libebml versions.

use the base FindNextElt in FindNextElt with optional creation

This is exactly the same code.
reuse AddNewElt() in FindNextElt()
reuse AddNewElt() in FindFirstElt()
